@page "/help"


<h1>How to Use Monica Interface</h1>


<div>

    <p>
        To use Monica service you need to have at least 4 files with
        these names: Sim.json Site.json, Crop.json, and Climate.csv.  You may also need
        a few JSON files as parameters.
    </p>

    <p>
        Since this web interface does not have access to users’
        local directories, you need to upload your Sim, Site, Crop and Climate files
        into the program, and if there is any link to the parameters, those JSON parameter
        files should be accessible in your github repository. So the program can read
        them from your github repository.
    </p>

    <p>
        Note: You can also use this program if any of these files
        are missing (we will use some default data), but remember; this case is only
        for testing purposes (e.g. for students).
    </p>

    <p><b>Login to your github</b></p>

    <p>
        You can find the login box on the top right of the Home page.
        You will be redirected to the Github login page to enter your Github User name and Password. If you are already logged into your Github on the same browser,
        and this is not your first login, you may not even asked to enter your data.
    </p>
    <p>Monica App needs to access to your public github repository to read the Monica parameters or to commit you result,
    so you need to permit Github to let Monica App has this access, if you are asked on the login page.</p>

    <p>
        <img width=750 height=541
             src="help/image001-2.jpg">
    </p>

    <p>&nbsp;</p>

    <p>
        If you don’t log in to your github, you can
        still use this program, but some features will not be available/visable.
    </p>

    <p class=MsoListParagraphCxSpLast>&nbsp;</p>

    <p><b>Upload Data:</b></p>

    <p>
        Use this page to upload your Sim, Site, Crop,
        and climate files. (sim, site and crop files are in JSON format and the climate
        file is in CSV format).
    </p>

    <p>
        <img width=751 height=532 id="Picture 3"
             src="help/image002.jpg">
    </p>

    <p>
        Be careful that the name of the files must
        correctly start with (sim/site/crop or climate). Please note that if you upload
        two or more files with the same structure (e.g. two sim files), the system will
        ignore the second one and you may confuse which file has been used to make the
        result.
    </p>

    <p>
        Please note that if you don’t upload one of
        these files, the system will ask you a confirmation and then you need to
        approve that a sample file will be used instead of the missing file. (We
        activated these default values only for educational purposes).
    </p>

    <p>&nbsp;</p>

    <p>&nbsp;</p>

    <p>
        If you are logged into your github, you
        will have some options at the bottom of this page.
    </p>

    <p>
        <b>
            Read Monica parameters from the Default
            server:
        </b> will read the parameters form sample data if it is mentioned in
        your sim/site/crop file.
    </p>

    <p>
        <b>Read Monica parameters from your github</b>:
        will show you a box to enter your parameters path in your github repository.
        You can copy the path from your browser when you are in your github. Please see
        the image blew
    </p>

    <p>
        <img width=752 height=538
             src="help/image003.jpg">
    </p>

    <p>&nbsp;</p>

    <p>
        Please note that this app will ignore the “include-file-base-path”
        option inside your sim/crop/site and will use the path which is defined here in
        this page. This is especially notable for old Monica users who needed to set the
        path of the parameters inside the main files.
    </p>

    <p>&nbsp;</p>

    <p>&nbsp;</p>

    <p>
        When you send your request to the Monica
        ZMQ server, the app needs some time to read and merge your data, send it to the
        simulator and show the result to you. If your files are big or you have many
        parameters, reading from your local machine or github is not real-time and
        takes a little bit of time. So after click on the "Send" button please be patient.
    </p>

    <p>&nbsp;</p>

    <p>
        This app can also provide the results in
        two ways for you.
    </p>

    <p>
        <b>Show me a download link:</b> your result
        will be saved on our server for a few days. You can download the results in
        JSON and CSV format or you can copy the link and share it with other people. So
        others just need to have this unique link to see your result. We recommend you
        to download your result if you need it for further use, because depending on
        the server load, old results will be deleted time by time.
    </p>

    <p>&nbsp;</p>

    <p>
        <b>Export into my github</b>: This option
        will ask you a path to your github to put/commit your results there. We suggest
        you to use the same path as your parameters on your github.
    </p>

    <p>
        Please note that the path is absolute and
        doesn’t have “/” at its end.
    </p>

    <p class=MsoListParagraphCxSpLast>&nbsp;</p>

    <p><b>Results’ chart</b></p>

