    <p><b>Settings:</b></p>

    <p>
        <img width=752 height=469 id="Picture 11"
             src="help/image014.jpg">
    </p>

    <p>&nbsp;</p>

    <p>
        Setting page contains very important information
        about the Monica ZMQ server. You need to ask about the right configuration
        before using this program. There are probably some default settings here, but
        you need to be sure these are addressing a right Monica ZMQ server.
    </p>

    <p>
        To change a setting you just need to
        replace the default value. (There is no save button, it will be saved
        automatically.)
    </p>

    <p>
        If you have logged into your github
        account, you may see your repository name in the “User Name” field.
    </p>

    <p>
        <b>Github Path Validator:</b> is a tool, to
        check whether the app has access to read your parameters correctly or not. (Use
        this tool when you are logged-in.)
    </p>

    <p>
        If you enter a right path; by clicking on
        the “Validate the path” button, a green checkmark icon will be shown.
    </p>

    <p>
        <img width=751 height=537 id="Picture 14"
             src="help/image015.jpg">
    </p>

    <p>&nbsp;</p>

    <p>&nbsp;</p>

    <p>
        If you are logged-in, your setting form the
        setting page and your github paths (parameters and export path) will be saved
        on your browser’s local storage, so next time you use this service you don’t
        need to fill these fields again, but if you use a different browser, you need
        to log-in again. In this case, you can save different settings (by the same or a
        different github user) it also means that you cannot reach your previous
        settings by logging-in from different browsers. But in the same browser your
        setting will remain valid even after closing the browser. If you want to clear
        the setting you need to logout.
    </p>

    <p>&nbsp;</p>

</div>